text.section:
As used in this section:
"Settlement trust" means the national tobacco grower settlement trust established between tobacco companies and states with tobacco growers and tobacco quota owners in accordance with the master settlement agreement between certain tobacco companies and states' attorneys general dated November 23, 1998;
"Settlement trust agreement" means the agreement to provide economic assistance from the national tobacco grower settlement trust directly to tobacco growers and tobacco quota holders in the Commonwealth;
"Trustee of the settlement trust" means the entity legally responsible for management of the national tobacco grower settlement trust; and
"Corporation" means the Kentucky Tobacco Settlement Trust Corporation created by this section.

The corporation shall be directed by a board of directors, which shall include:
The Governor, who shall serve as chair of the corporation;
The Commissioner of Agriculture, who shall serve as vice chair of the corporation;
The Attorney General, who shall serve as secretary of the corporation;
One (1) member of the Senate appointed by the President of the Senate to serve as an ex officio, nonvoting member of the board;
One (1) member of the House of Representatives appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives to serve as an ex officio, nonvoting member of the board;
Six (6) citizen members who are tobacco growers or tobacco quota owners appointed by the Governor for a term of four (4) years;
One (1) citizen member with a distinguished record of public service appointed by the Governor for a term of four (4) years; and
Two (2) members appointed by the Governor for a term of four (4) years from a list of six (6) nominees selected and submitted to the Governor by the state's congressional delegation.

The corporation's duties shall include, but not be limited to:
Performing all duties and responsibilities of a state certification body as defined and directed under the terms of the settlement trust agreement;
Preparing and submitting a plan to the trustee of the settlement trust for its approval. The plan shall identify those tobacco growers and tobacco quota owners who are to receive direct payment from the settlement trust and shall determine the respective amount each of the tobacco growers or tobacco quota owners is to receive;
Determining the amount of any administrative expenses to be paid to the corporation under the terms of the settlement trust agreement;
Appointing an officer to conduct executive functions for the corporation. The officer may be a state officer or employee who shall serve as a borrowed servant at no cost to the corporation;
Requesting the trustee of the settlement trust to set aside reserve amounts in anticipation of a decrease in annual payments;
Submitting information required by the trustee of the settlement trust;
Establishing policies and procedures and contracting with other persons or entities if necessary to effectuate its purposes and functions;
Discharging additional powers, duties, and functions as necessary or convenient to carry out the purposes of this section;
Enacting bylaws concerning the conduct of its business and other administrative procedures as it deems necessary;
Provide for the distribution of state funds appropriated in 2005 Ky. Acts ch. 173, Parts I and II to the beneficiaries of the National Tobacco Growers Settlement Trust in a manner consistent with this section; and
Provide for the distribution of one (1) time payments under the amnesty compensation program described in subsection (8) of this section.
